  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">TB Local Organizations Network (LON)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Zambia):  TB LON is USAID/Zambia&apos;s premiere local TB award, a key component of  the Accelerator to End TB  initiative to double the decline in TB incidence and ultimately end TB by 2030. This mechanism  will work in Lusaka and Southern Province to close gaps in TB elimination activities in specific populations with high TB burdens, including underserved communities, people in congregate settings such as prisons, mining communities, children, and people living with HIV/AIDS. Using FY 2020 resources the mechanism will focus on: revision and dissemination of updated guidelines; infection control; intensified and active TB case finding, treatment and prevention activities; and capacity building in various areas of TB control. TB LON will build on existing USAID investment through our bilateral Eradicate TB and will leverage PEPFAR as well as other partner and stakeholder funding to implement interventions and ensure provision of essential prevention and treatment services for TB with a view to build sustainability. Under USAID&apos;s Country Development Cooperation Strategy, the mechanism will support Development Objective 3: Capacity of Zambia&apos;s Government, Citizens and Private Sector Increased to Improve Health Outcomes and Meet Critical Needs of Vulnerable Populations... .</narrative>
  </description>
